quran[339]{c,v,t}:
  25,21,"Say those who look not to encounter Us, 'Why have the angels not been sent down on us, or why see we not our Lord?' Waxed proud they have within them, and become greatly disdainful"
  25,22,"Upon the day that they see the angels, no good tidings that day for the sinners; they shall say, 'A ban forbidden"
  25,23,"We shall advance upon what work they have done, and make it a scattered dust"
  25,24,"The inhabitants of Paradise that day, better shall be their lodging, fairer their resting-place"
  25,25,Upon the day that heaven is split asunder with the clouds and the angels are sent down in majesty
  25,26,"the Kingdom that day, the true Kingdom, shall belong to the All-merciful and it shall be a day harsh for the unbelievers"
  25,27,"Upon the day the evildoer shall bite his hands, saying, 'Would that I had taken a way along with the Messenger"
  25,28,"Alas, would that I had not taken So-and-so for a friend"
  25,29,"He indeed led me astray from the Remembrance, after it had come to me; Satan is ever a forsaker of men"
  25,30,"The Messenger says, 'O my Lord, behold, my people have taken this Koran as a thing to be shunned"
  25,31,Even so We have appointed to every Prophet an enemy among the sinners; but thy Lord suffices as a guide and as a helper
  25,32,"The unbelievers say, 'Why has the Koran not been sent down upon him all at once?' Even so, that We may strengthen thy heart thereby, and We have chanted it very distinctly"
  25,33,"They bring not to thee any similitude but that We bring thee the truth, and better in exposition"
  25,34,"Those who shall be mustered to Gehenna upon their faces -- they shall be worse in place, and gone further astray from the way"
  25,35,"We gave Moses the Book, and appointed with him his brother Aaron as minister"
  25,36,"and We said, 'Go to the people who have cried lies to Our signs'; then We destroyed them utterly"
  25,37,"And the people of Noah, when they cried lies to the Messengers, We drowned them, and made them to be a sign to mankind; and We have prepared for the evildoers a painful chastisement"
  25,38,"And Ad, and Thamood, and the men of Er-Rass, and between that generations a many"
  25,39,"for each We struck similitudes, and each We ruined utterly"
  25,40,"Surely they have come by the city that was rained on by an evil rain; what, have they not seen it? Nay, but they look for no upraising"
  25,41,"And when they see thee, they take thee in mockery only: 'What, is this he whom God sent forth as a Messenger"
  25,42,"Wellnigh he had led us astray from our gods, but that we kept steadfast to them.' Assuredly they shall know, when they see the chastisement, who is further astray from the way"
  25,43,Hast thou seen him who has taken his caprice to be his god? Wilt thou be a guardian over them
  25,44,"Or deemest thou that most of them hear or understand? They are but as the cattle; nay, they are further astray from the way"
  25,45,"Hast thou not regarded thy Lord, how He has stretched out the shadow? Had He willed, He would have made it still. Then We appointed the sun, to be a guide to it"
  25,46,"thereafter We seize it to Ourselves, drawing it gently"
  25,47,"It is He who appointed the night for you to be a garment and sleep for a rest, and day He appointed for a rising"
  25,48,"And it is He who has loosed the winds, bearing good tidings before His mercy; and We sent down from heaven pure water"
  25,49,"so that We might revive a dead land, and give to drink of it, of that We created, cattle and men a many"
  25,50,"We have indeed turned it about amongst them, so that they may remember; yet most men refuse all but unbelief"
  25,51,"If We had willed, We would have raised up in every city a warner"
  25,52,"So obey not the unbelievers, but struggle with them thereby mightily"
  25,53,"And it is He who let forth the two seas, this one Sweet, grateful to taste, and this salt, bitter to the tongue, and He set between them a barrier, and a ban forbidden"
  25,54,"And it is He who created of water a mortal, and made him kindred of blood and marriage; thy Lord is All-powerful"
  25,55,"And they serve, apart from God, what neither profits them nor hurts them; and the unbeliever is ever a partisan against his Lord"
  25,56,"We have sent thee not, except good tidings to bear, and warning"
  25,57,"Say: 'I do not ask of you a wage for this, except for him who wishes to take to his Lord a way"
  25,58,"Put thy trust in the Living God, the Undying, and proclaim His praise. Sufficiently is He aware of His servants sins"
  25,59,"who created the heavens and the earth, and what between them is, in six days, then sat Himself upon the Throne, the All-compassionate: ask any informed of Him"
  25,60,"But when they are told, 'Bow yourselves to the All-merciful,' they say, 'And what is the All-merciful? Shall we bow ourselves to what thou biddest us?' And it increases them in aversion"
  25,61,"Blessed be He who has set in heaven constellations, and has set among them a lamp, and an illuminating moon"
  25,62,And it is He who made the night and day a succession for whom He desires to remember or He desires to be thankful
  25,63,"The servants of the All-merciful are those who walk in the earth modestly and who, when the ignorant address them, say, 'Peace"
  25,64,who pass the night prostrate to their Lord and standing
  25,65,"who say, 'Our Lord, turn Thou from us the chastisement of Gehenna; surely its chastisement is torment most terrible"
  25,66,evil it is as a lodging-place and an abode
  25,67,"who, when they expend, are neither prodigal nor parsimonious, but between that is a just stand"
  25,68,"who call not upon another god with God, nor slay the soul God has forbidden except by right, neither fornicate, for whosoever does that shall meet the price"
  25,69,"of sin-doubled shall be the chastisement for him on the Resurrection Day, and he shall dwell therein humbled"
  25,70,"save him who repents, and believes, and does righteous work -- those, God will change their evil deeds into good deeds, for God is ever All-forgiving, All-compassionate"
  25,71,"and whosoever repents, and does righteousness, he truly turns to God in repentance"
  25,72,"And those who bear not false witness and, when they pass by idle talk, pass by with dignity"
  25,73,"who, when they are reminded of the signs of their Lord, fall not down thereat deaf and blind"
  25,74,"who say, 'Our Lord, give us refreshment of our wives and seed, and make us a model to the godfearing"
  25,75,"Those shall be recompensed with the highest heaven, for that they endured patiently, and they shall receive therein a greeting and --' Peace"
  25,76,Therein they shall dwell forever; fair it is as a lodging-place and an abode
  25,77,"Say: 'My Lord esteems you not at all were it not for your prayer, for you have cried lies, and it shall surely be fastened"
  26,1,Ta Sin Mim
  26,2,Those are the signs of the Manifest Book
  26,3,Perchance thou consumest thyself that they are not believers
  26,4,"If We will, We shall send down on them out of heaven a sign, so their necks will stay humbled to it"
  26,5,"But never fresh remembrance comes to them from the All-merciful, except they turn away from it"
  26,6,So they have cried lies; therefore assuredly tidings will come to them of that they mocked at
  26,7,"What, have they not regarded the earth, how many therein We have caused to grow of every generous kind"
  26,8,"Surely in that is a sign, yet most of them are not believers"
  26,9,"Surely thy Lord, He is the All-mighty, the All-compassionate"
  26,10,"And when thy Lord called to Moses, 'Go to the people of the evildoers"
  26,11,the people of Pharaoh; will they not be godfearing
  26,12,"He said, 'My Lord, I fear they will cry me lies"
  26,13,"and my breast will be straitened, and my tongue will not be loosed; so send to Aaron"
  26,14,"They also have a sin against me, and I fear they will slay me"
  26,15,"Said He, 'No indeed; but go, both of you, with Our signs, and We assuredly shall be with you, listening"
  26,16,"So go you to Pharaoh, and say, \"Verily, I am the Messenger of the Lord of all Being"
  26,17,so send forth with us the Children of Israel
  26,18,"He said, 'Did we not raise thee amongst us as a child? Didst thou not tarry among us years of thy life"
  26,19,"And thou didst the deed thou didst, being one of the ungrateful"
  26,20,"Said he, 'Indeed I did it then, being one of those that stray"
  26,21,"so I fled from you, fearing you. But my Lord gave me Judgment and made me one of the Envoys"
  26,22,"That is a blessing thou reproachest me with, having enslaved the Children of Israel"
  26,23,"Pharaoh said, 'And what is the Lord of all Being"
  26,24,"He said, 'The Lord of the heavens and earth, and what between them is, if you have faith"
  26,25,"Said he to those about him, 'Do you not hear"
  26,26,"He said, 'Your Lord and the Lord of your fathers, the ancients"
  26,27,"Said he, 'Surely your Messenger who was sent to you is possessed"
  26,28,"He said, 'The Lord of the East and West, and what between them is, if you have understanding"
  26,29,"Said he, 'If thou takest a god other than me, I shall surely make thee one of the imprisoned"
  26,30,"He said, 'What, even though I brought thee something so manifest"
  26,31,"Said he, 'Bring it then, if thou art of the truthful"
  26,32,"So he cast his staff, and behold, it was a serpent manifest"
  26,33,"And he drew forth his hand, and lo, it was white to the beholders"
  26,34,"Said he to the Council about him, 'Surely this man is a cunning sorcerer"
  26,35,who desires to expel you from your land by his sorcery; what do you command
  26,36,"They said, 'Put him and his brother off a while, and send among the cities musterers"
  26,37,to bring thee every cunning sorcerer
  26,38,So the sorcerers were assembled for the appointed time of a fixed day
  26,39,"The people were asked, 'Will you assemble"
  26,40,Haply we shall follow the sorcerers if it should be they are the victors
  26,41,"Then, when the sorcerers came, they said to Pharaoh, 'Shall we indeed have a wage, if we should be the victors"
  26,42,"He said, 'Yes indeed; and you shall then be among the near-stationed"
  26,43,"Moses said to them, 'Cast you down what you will cast"
  26,44,"So they cast their ropes and their staffs, and said, 'By the might of Pharaoh we shall be the victors"
  26,45,"Then Moses cast his staff and lo, it forthwith swallowed up their lying invention"
  26,46,"so the sorcerers were cast down, bowing themselves"
  26,47,"They said, 'We believe in the Lord of all Being"
  26,48,the Lord of Moses and Aaron
  26,49,"Said Pharaoh, 'You have believed him before I gave you leave. Why, he is the chief of you, the same that taught you sorcery; now you shall know! I shall assuredly cut off alternately your hands and feet, then I shall crucify you all together"
  26,50,"They said, 'There is no harm; surely unto our Lord we are turning"
  26,51,"We are eager that our Lord should forgive us our offences, for that we are the first of the believers"
  26,52,"Also We revealed unto Moses, 'Go with My servants by night; surely you will be followed"
  26,53,Then Pharaoh sent among the cities musterers
  26,54,"Behold, these are a small troop"
  26,55,and indeed they are enraging us
  26,56,and we are a host on our guard
  26,57,So We expelled them from gardens and fountains
  26,58,and treasures and a noble station
  26,59,"even so, and We bequeathed them upon the Children of Israel"
  26,60,Then they followed them at the sunrise
  26,61,"and, when the two hosts sighted each other, the companions of Moses said, 'We are overtaken"
  26,62,"Said he, 'No indeed; surely my Lord is with me; He will guide me"
  26,63,"Then We revealed to Moses, 'Strike with thy staff the sea'; and it clave, and each part was as a mighty mount"
  26,64,And there We brought the others on
  26,65,and We delivered Moses and those with him all together
  26,66,then We drowned the others
  26,67,"Surely in that is a sign, yet most of them are not believers"
  26,68,"Surely thy Lord, He is the All-mighty, the All-compassionate"
  26,69,And recite to them the tiding of Abraham
  26,70,"when he said to his father and his people, 'What do you serve"
  26,71,"They said, 'We serve idols, and continue cleaving to them"
  26,72,"He said, 'Do they hear you when you call"
  26,73,"or do they profit you, or harm"
  26,74,"They said, 'Nay, but we found our fathers so doing"
  26,75,"He said, 'And have you considered what you have been serving"
  26,76,"you and your fathers, the elders"
  26,77,"They are an enemy to me, except the Lord of all Being"
  26,78,"who created me, and Himself guides me"
  26,79,and Himself gives me to eat and drink
  26,80,"and, whenever I am sick, heals me"
  26,81,"who makes me to die, then gives me life"
  26,82,and who I am eager shall forgive me my offence on the Day of Doom
  26,83,"My Lord, give me Judgment, and join me with the righteous"
  26,84,and appoint me a tongue of truthfulness among the others
  26,85,Make me one of the inheritors of the Garden of Bliss
  26,86,"and forgive my father, for he is one of those astray"
  26,87,Degrade me not upon the day when they are raised up
  26,88,the day when neither wealth nor sons shall profit
  26,89,except for him who comes to God with a pure heart
  26,90,And Paradise shall be brought forward for the godfearing
  26,91,and Hell advanced for the perverse
  26,92,"It shall be said to them, 'Where is that you were serving"
  26,93,apart from God? Do they help you or help themselves
  26,94,"Then they shall be pitched into it, they and the perverse"
  26,95,"and the hosts of Iblis, all together"
  26,96,"They shall say, as they dispute there one with another"
  26,97,"By God, we were certainly in manifest error"
  26,98,when we made you equal with the Lord of all Being
  26,99,It was naught but the sinners that led us astray
  26,100,so now we have no intercessors
  26,101,no loyal friend
  26,102,"O that we might return again, and be among the believers"
  26,103,"Surely in that is a sign, yet most of them are not believers"
  26,104,"Surely thy Lord, He is the All-mighty, the All-compassionate"
  26,105,The people of Noah cried lies to the Envoys
  26,106,"when their brother Noah said to them, 'Will you not be godfearing"
  26,107,I am for you a faithful Messenger
  26,108,"so serve you God, and obey you me"
  26,109,I ask of you no wage for this; my wage falls only upon the Lord of all Being
  26,110,"so fear you God, and obey you me"
  26,111,"They said, 'Shall we believe thee, whom the vilest follow"
  26,112,"He said, 'What knowledge have I of that they have been doing"
  26,113,"Their account falls only upon my Lord, were you but aware"
  26,114,I would not drive away the believers
  26,115,I am naught but a plain warner
  26,116,"They said, 'If thou givest not over, Noah, thou shalt assuredly be one of the stoned"
  26,117,"He said, 'My Lord, my people have cried me lies"
  26,118,"so give true deliverance between me and them, and deliver me and the believers that are with me"
  26,119,"So We delivered him, and those with him, in the laden ship"
  26,120,then afterwards We drowned the rest
  26,121,"Surely in that is a sign, yet most of them are not believers"
  26,122,"Surely thy Lord, He is the All-mighty, the All-compassionate"
  26,123,Ad cried lies to the Envoys
  26,124,"when their brother Hood said to them, 'Will you not be godfearing"
  26,125,I am for you a faithful Messenger
  26,126,"so fear you God, and obey you me"
  26,127,I ask of you no wage for this; my wage falls only upon the Lord of all Being
  26,128,"What, do you build on every prominence a sign, sporting"
  26,129,"and do you take to you castles, haply to dwell forever"
  26,130,"When you assault, you assault like tyrants"
  26,131,"So fear you God, and obey you me"
  26,132,and fear Him who has succoured you with what you know
  26,133,succoured you with flocks and sons
  26,134,gardens and fountains
  26,135,"Indeed, I fear for you the chastisement of a dreadful day"
  26,136,"They said, 'Alike it is to us, whether thou admonishest, or art not one of the admonishers"
  26,137,this is nothing but the habit of the ancients
  26,138,and we shall not be chastised
  26,139,"So they cried him lies; then We destroyed them. Surely in that is a sign, yet most of them are not believers"
  26,140,"Surely thy Lord, He is the All-mighty, the All-compassionate"
  26,141,Thamood cried lies to the Envoys
  26,142,"when their brother Salih said to them, 'Will you not be godfearing"
  26,143,I am for you a faithful Messenger
  26,144,"so fear you God, and obey you me"
  26,145,I ask of you no wage for this; my wage falls only upon the Lord of all Being
  26,146,Will you be left secure in this here
  26,147,among gardens and fountains
  26,148,"sown fields, and palms with slender spathes"
  26,149,Will you still skilfully hew houses out of the mountains
  26,150,"So fear you God, and obey you me"
  26,151,and obey not the commandment of the prodigal
  26,152,"who do corruption in the earth, and set not things aright"
  26,153,"They said, 'Thou art merely one of those that are bewitched"
  26,154,"thou art naught but a mortal, like us; then produce a sign, if thou art one of the truthful"
  26,155,"He said, 'This is a she-camel; to her a draught and to you a draught, on a day appointed"
  26,156,and do not touch her with malice so that there seize you the chastisement of a dreadful day
  26,157,"But they hamstrung her, and in the morning they were remorseful"
  26,158,"and the chastisement seized them. Surely in that is a sign, yet most of them are not believers"
  26,159,"Surely thy Lord, He is the All-mighty, the All-compassionate"
  26,160,The people of Lot cried lies to the Envoys
  26,161,"when their brother Lot said to them, 'Will you not be godfearing"
  26,162,I am for you a faithful Messenger
  26,163,"so fear you God, and obey you me"
  26,164,I ask of you no wage for this; my wage falls only upon the Lord of all Being
  26,165,"What, do you come to male beings"
  26,166,"leaving your wives that your Lord created for you? Nay, but you are a people of transgressors"
  26,167,"They said, 'If thou givest not over, Lot, thou shalt assuredly be one of the expelled"
  26,168,"He said, 'Truly I am a detester of what you do"
  26,169,"My Lord, deliver me and my people from that they do"
  26,170,So We delivered him and his people all together
  26,171,save an old woman among those that tarried
  26,172,then We destroyed the others
  26,173,and We rained on them a rain; and evil is the rain of them that are warned
  26,174,"Surely in that is a sign, yet most of them are not believers"
  26,175,"Surely thy Lord, He is the All-mighty, the All-compassionate"
  26,176,The men of the Thicket cried lies to the Envoys
  26,177,"when Shuaib said to them, 'Will you not be godfearing"
  26,178,"I am for you a faithful Messenger, so fear you God, and obey you me"
  26,179,I ask of you no wage for this
  26,180,my wage falls only upon the Lord of all Being
  26,181,"Fill up the measure, and be not cheaters"
  26,182,and weigh with the straight balance
  26,183,"and diminish not the goods of the people, and do not mischief in the earth, working corruption"
  26,184,"Fear Him who created you, and the generations of the ancients"
  26,185,"They said, 'Thou art merely one of those that are bewitched"
  26,186,"thou art naught but a mortal, like us; indeed, we think that thou art one of the liars"
  26,187,"Then drop down on us lumps from heaven, if thou art one of the truthful"
  26,188,"He said, 'My Lord knows very well what you are doing"
  26,189,But they cried him lies; then there seized them the chastisement of the Day of Shadow; assuredly it was the chastisement of a dreadful day
  26,190,"Surely in that is a sign, yet most of them are not believers"
  26,191,"Surely thy Lord, He is the All-mighty, the All-compassionate"
  26,192,Truly it is the revelation of the Lord of all Being
  26,193,brought down by the Faithful Spirit
  26,194,"upon thy heart, that thou mayest be one of the warners"
  26,195,"in a clear, Arabic tongue"
  26,196,Truly it is in the Scriptures of the ancients
  26,197,"Was it not a sign for them, that it is known to the learned of the Children of Israel"
  26,198,If We had sent it down on a barbarian
  26,199,"and he had recited it to them, they would not have believed in it"
  26,200,Even so We have caused it to enter into the hearts of the sinners
  26,201,"who will not believe in it, until they see the painful chastisement"
  26,202,"so that it will come upon them suddenly, while they are not aware"
  26,203,"and they will say, 'Shall we be respited"
  26,204,"What, do they seek to hasten Our chastisement"
  26,205,What thinkest thou? If We give them enjoyment of days for many years
  26,206,then there comes on them that they were promised
  26,207,"what will it then avail them, the enjoyment of days they were given"
  26,208,"Never a city We destroyed, but it had warners"
  26,209,for a reminder; and never did We wrong
  26,210,Not by the Satans has it been brought down
  26,211,"it behoves them not, neither are they able"
  26,212,"Truly, they are expelled from hearing"
  26,213,"So call thou not upon another god with God, lest thou shouldst be one of those that are chastised"
  26,214,"And warn thy clan, thy nearest kin"
  26,215,"Lower thy wing to those who follow thee, being believers"
  26,216,"then, if they disobey thee, say, 'I am quit of that you do"
  26,217,"Put thy trust in the All-mighty, the All-compassionate"
  26,218,who sees thee when thou standest
  26,219,and when thou turnest about among those who bow
  26,220,"Surely He is the All-hearing, the All-knowing"
  26,221,Shall I tell you on whom the Satans come down
  26,222,They come down on every guilty impostor
  26,223,"They give ear, but most of them are liars"
  26,224,And the poets -- the perverse follow them
  26,225,hast thou not seen how they wander in every valley
  26,226,and how they say that which they do not
  26,227,"Save those that believe, and do righteous deeds, and remember God oft, and help themselves after being wronged; and those who do wrong shall surely know by what overturning they will he overturned"
  27,1,Ta Sin. Those are the signs of the Koran and a Manifest Book
  27,2,"a guidance, and good tidings unto the believers"
  27,3,"who perform the prayer, and pay the alms, and have sure faith in the Hereafter"
  27,4,"Those who believe not in the Hereafter, We have decked out fair for them their works, and they wander blindly"
  27,5,"those are they whom an evil chastisement awaits, and they will be the greatest losers in the Hereafter"
  27,6,"Thou receivest the Koran from One All-wise, All-knowing"
  27,7,"When Moses said to his people 'I observe a fire, and will bring you news of it, or I will bring you a flaming brand, that haply you shall warm yourselves"
  27,8,"So, when he came to it, he was called: 'Blessed is he who is in the fire, and he who is about it. Glory be to God, the Lord of all Being"
  27,9,"Moses, behold, it is I, God, the All-mighty, the All-wise"
  27,10,"Cast down thy staff.' And when he saw it quivering like a serpent he turned about, retreating, and turned not back. 'Moses, fear not; surely the Envoys do not fear in My presence"
  27,11,"save him who has done evil, then; after evil, has changed into good; All-forgiving am I, All-compassionate"
  27,12,Thrust thy hand in thy bosom and it will come forth white without evil-among nine signs to Pharaoh and his people; they are an ungodly people
  27,13,"But when Our signs came to them visibly, they said, 'This is a manifest sorcery"
  27,14,"and they denied them, though their souls acknowledged them, wrongfully and out of pride. Behold, how was the end of the workers of corruption"
  27,15,"And We gave David and Solomon knowledge and they said, 'Praise belongs to God who has preferred us over many of His believing servants"
  27,16,"And Solomon was David's heir, and he said, 'Men, we have been taught the speech of the birds, and we have been given of everything; surely this is indeed the manifest bounty"
  27,17,"And his hosts were mustered to Solomon, jinn, men and birds, duly disposed"
  27,18,"till, when they came on the Valley of Ants, an ant said, 'Ants, enter your dwelling-places, lest Solomon and his hosts crush you, being unaware"
  27,19,"But he smiled, laughing at its words, and he said, 'My Lord, dispose me that I may be thankful for Thy blessing wherewith Thou hast blessed me and my father and mother, and that I may do righteousness well-pleasing to Thee; and do Thou admit me, by Thy mercy, amongst Thy righteous servants"
  27,20,"And he reviewed the birds; then he said, 'How is it with me, that I do not see the hoopoe? Or is he among the absent"
  27,21,"Assuredly I will chastise him with a terrible chastisement, or I will slaughter him, or he bring me a clear authority"
  27,22,"But he tarried not long, and said, 'I have comprehended that which thou hast not comprehended, and I have come from Sheba to thee with a sure tiding"
  27,23,"I found a woman ruling over them, and she has been given of everything, and she possesses a mighty throne"
  27,24,"I found her and her people prostrating to the sun, apart from God; Satan has decked out fair their deeds to them and he has barred them from the way, and therefore they are not guided"
  27,25,"so that they prostrate not themselves to God, who brings forth what is hidden in the heavens and earth; and He knows what you conceal and what you publish"
  27,26,"God: there is no god but He, the Lord of the Mighty Throne"
  27,27,"Said he, 'Now We will see whether thou hast spoken truly, or whether thou art amongst those that lie"
  27,28,"Take this letter of mine, and cast it unto them, then turn back from them and see what they shall return"
  27,29,"She said, 'O Council, see, a letter honourable has been cast unto me"
  27,30,"It is from Solomon, and it is \"In the Name of God, the Merciful, the Compassionate"
  27,31,"Rise not up against me, but come to me in surrender"
  27,32,"She said, 'O Council, pronounce to me concerning my affair; I am not used to decide an affair until you bear me witness"
  27,33,"They said, 'We possess force and we possess great might. The affair rests with thee; so consider what thou wilt command"
  27,34,"She said, 'Kings, when they enter a city, disorder it and make the mighty ones of its inhabitants abased. Even so they too will do"
  27,35,"Now I will send them a present, and see what the envoys bring back"
  27,36,"But when he came to Solomon he said, 'What, would you succour me with wealth, and what God gave me is better than what He has given you? Nay, but instead you rejoice in your gift"
  27,37,"Return thou to them; we shall assuredly come against them with hosts they have not power to resist, and we shall expel them from there, abased and utterly humbled"
  27,38,"He said, 'O Council, which one of you will bring me her throne, before they come to me in surrender"
  27,39,"An efreet of the jinns said, 'I will bring it to thee, before thou risest from thy place; I have strength for it"
  27,40,"and I am trusty.' Said he who possessed knowledge of the Book, 'I will bring it to thee, before ever thy glance returns to thee.' Then, when he saw it settled before him, he said, 'This is of my Lord's bounty that He may try me, whether I am thankful or ungrateful. Whosoever gives thanks gives thanks only for his own soul's good, and whosoever is ungrateful -- my Lord is surely All-sufficient, All-generous"
  27,41,"He said, 'Disguise her throne for her, and we shall behold whether she is guided or if she is of those that are not guided"
  27,42,"So, when she came, it was said, 'Is thy throne like this?' She said, 'It seems the same.' 'And we were given the knowledge before her, and we were in surrender"
  27,43,"but that she served, apart from God, barred her, for she was of a people of unbelievers"
  27,44,"It was said to her, 'Enter the pavilion.' But when she saw it, she supposed it was a spreading water, and she bared her legs. He said, 'It is a pavilion smoothed of crystal. She said, 'My Lord, indeed I have wronged myself, and I surrender with Solomon to God, the Lord of all Being"
  27,45,"And We sent to Thamood their brother Salih: 'Serve you God!' And behold, they were two parties, that were disputing one with another"
  27,46,"He said, 'O my people, why do you seek to hasten evil before good? Why do you not ask forgiveness of God? Haply so you will find mercy"
  27,47,"They said, 'We augur ill of thee and of those that are with thee.' He said, 'Your augury is with God; nay, but you are a people being proved"
  27,48,"Now in the city there were nine persons who did corruption in the land, and put not things right"
  27,49,"they said, 'Swear you, one to another, by God, \"We will attack him and his family by night, then we will tell his protector, We were not witnesses of the destruction of his family; and assuredly we are truthful men"
  27,50,"And they devised a device, and We likewise devised a device, while they were not aware"
  27,51,"and behold, how was the end of their device! For We destroyed them and their people all together"
  27,52,"Those are their houses, all fallen down because of the evil they committed; surely in that is a sign for a people who have knowledge"
  27,53,And We delivered those who believed and were godfearing
  27,54,"And Lot, when he said to his people, 'What, do you commit indecency with your eyes open"
  27,55,"What, do you approach men lustfully instead of women? No, you are a people that are ignorant"